'Kings Canyon National Park' is a national park in the southern Sierra Nevada,
east of Fresno, California. The park was established in 1940 and covers . It incorporated General Grant National Park, established in 1890
to protect the General Grant Grove of giant sequoias.

The park is north of and contiguous with Sequoia National Park; the two are
administered by the National Park Service jointly.
